text: Dane Dobbie (born December 1, 1986 in Elora, Ontario) is a professional lacrosse player for the Calgary Roughnecks in the National Lacrosse League. Dobbie comes from a lacrosse family. His grandfather, Bob Dobbie, is a member of Canadian Lacrosse Hall of Fame and his father Larry also competed at a high level. He was the MVP of the 2018-19 NLL season. ==References== Category:1986 births Category:Living people Category:Calgary Roughnecks players Category:Canadian lacrosse players Category:Lacrosse forwards Category:Sportspeople from Ontario
